t1991.text: Oh and I just remembered something. Usually, Gran would call us on our birthdays. Every single year without fail. Not getting that call just served as a sad reminder that she’s not here anymore.

t1992.text: We went home and mum asked me to help pick Gran’s funeral songs. We are supposed to go to bed early because mum and dad want us to go clothes shopping for the funeral. It has to be early because they are going to a musical. It’s already been arranged and they can’t change it.

t1993.text: We were supposed to get a cake but that didn’t happen. I didn’t say anything because it just seemed selfish to do so. I don’t even think I have the right to be complaining about this on here. Am I being an entitled brat?

t1994.text: That would’ve been nice but uncle Stephen struck again. He decided the meal I got was too big and made another comment on my weight. Mum and dad joined in. I just sat there awkwardly while they laughed. I think they were joking but I didn’t find it funny. Am I horrible?

t1995.text: Other people checked in as well. Honestly, that was the best part of my day. I did get presents and mum got me clothes. She said she knew some of my old ones didn’t fit and uncle Stephen commented on my weight. After that, we went to dinner.

t1996.text: It didn’t feel right to celebrate so soon after she died. My support worker thinks I should’ve done something nice for myself. She says I’m going to grieve for a long time so I should do something nice for myself. She called because she knew it was my birthday.

t1997.text: Well that was possibly the most depressing birthday in the universe. No one was home all day because they were running around getting stuff organised for Gran’s funeral. I didn’t really feel like I could celebrate my birthday because it seemed disrespectful.
